Comprehending ICMP

ICMP - resides at the network layer of the OSI model
Must be implemented by every IP module
No data is exchanged
Used to communicate updates or error messages
Used by the ping utility echo request/echo reply

ICMP Messages are two types - Error-reporting and Query

Error-Reporting
Type - 3  - Destination unreachable
Type - 4  - Source quench
Type - 11 - Time exceeded
Type - 12 - Parameter problem
Type - 5  - Redirection

Query
Type - 8/0  - Echo(request/reply)
Type - 13/14  - Timestamp (req./rep.)
Type - 18/18 - Address mask (req./rep.)
Type - 10/9 - Router solicitation/advertisement


IP Datagram - IPv6 Header 20 bytes - ICMP Message


0-7,8-15,16-31
8-bit type,8-bit code, 16-bit checksum
contents depend on type and code


ICMP Firewall rules

The only essential ICMP traffic is type 3
Optional types 0,8,11





Discovering ICMPv6

ICMPv6 - is used by IPv6 nodes to report errors encountered in processing packets, and to perform other internet-layer functions,
such as disgnostics (ICMPv6 "ping"). ICMPv6 is an integral part of IPv6, and the base protocol (all the messages nd behavior required
by this specification) MUST be fully implemented by every IPv6 Node.


ICMPv6

Must be implemented by every IP module
No data is exchanged
Used to communicate updates or error messages
Used by the ping utility echo request/echo reply



IP Datagram - IPv6 Header | ICMPv6 Message


